Description:
Ballistics of the 3VOF40 round with the 3OF29 shell and the 4Zh48 or 4Zh60 reduced-variable charge, fired from the 152.4mm towed-gun 2A36 "Giatsint-B", 2A37 gun as part of the self-propelled artillery 2S5 "Giatsint-S". Separate loading with copper cartridge.

From range table, the 4Zh48 charge consists of a mix of 12/7 and 9/7 grains. 4Zh60 contains 10/7 grains. For both charges, the full charge loads 11.0 kg and develops 775 m/s. Zone 1 loads 8.7 kg and develops 670 m/s. Zone 2 loads 6.4 kg and develops 560 m/s.

Barrel length, inclusive of muzzle device, is 8215 mm for 2S5 and 8197 mm for 2A36. Rifled length is the same as 6185 mm. Chamber length (breech to beginning of rifling) is 850 mm. Chamber volume is 27 L. Performance variation from АРТИЛЛЕРИЙСКИЕ МЕТАТЕЛЬНЫЕ ЗАРЯДЫ:
For the full charge:
T    mv   P.mcp
°C   m/s  kgf/cm²  MPa
-50  764  2880
 15  775  3200     351.2    
 50  788  3630
Pressure values are interpreted as copper-crusher gauge. Converted to piezoelectric values in MPa with factor 0.098 * 1.12.
